Radiology Reports

  • 04/05/2019 - Abdomino-Pelvic CT Scan: Technique: Plain and Triphasic IV Contrast enhanced axial CT Scan of abdomen and pelvis has been performed with retrospective 2D multiplanar reconstruction. LIVER, RETROPERITONEUM AND PANCREAS: Multiple small simple cysts are seen in all segments of the liver, with a particular predilection for segment 6. GALLBLADDER: Gallbladder is distended with normal wall thickness. It shows no hypersense calculi within. APPENDIX: CT depicts a fluid-filled distended appendix with periappendiceal fat-stranding. BOWEL: unremarkable. PERITONEUM: FREE ABDOMINAL SPACE: Evidence of free liquid within the subhepatic space. DIAGNOSTIC SUSPICION: Strong clinical suspicion for acute appendicitis.
  • 04/05/2019 - RLQ Ultrasound Emergent: Longitudinal and transverse sonogram show an enlarged appendix surrounded by hyperechoic inflamed fat. Power Doppler sonography shows hypervascularity of the appendiceal wall. Evidence of free liquid within the subhepatic space.
